<DOC><DOCNO> AP890306-0100 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-03-06-89 1603EST</FILEID><FIRST>r w AM-US-PalestinianThreat     03-06 0149</FIRST><SECOND>AM-US-Palestinian Threat,140</SECOND><HEAD>U.S. Condemns New Threat on Rushdie</HEAD><DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   The State Department condemned on Monday athreat by a radical Palestinian leader to carry out the orders ofIran's Ayatollah Ruhollah Khomeini to kill British author SalmanRushdie.   Department spokesman Charles Redman said the statement by AhmedJibril, leader of the Popular Front for the Liberation ofPalestine-General Command, ``highlights the menace'' posed by thatgroup and its association with Iran's state-sponsored terrorism.   ``This terrorist group is based in Damascus and therefore thegovernment in Syria has an obligation to exercise control over thegroup's actions,'' Redman said.   ``We call on Syria to take appropriate action to ensure thePFLP-GC does not follow through on this threat,'' he added.   Jibril said Sunday that Rushdie's novel, ``The Satanic Verses,''was a conspiracy to defame Islam and had been written at the behestof ``arrogant'' Western forces.</TEXT></DOC>